   "source": [
    "# MPC List API\n",
    "\n",
    "#### This tutorial provides information on how to use the Minor Planet Center's List API.\n",
    "\n",
    "The Minor Planet Center's `List` service returns lists of objects selected by object type.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is useful when you want to (e.g.):\n",
    " - Retrieve a list of all known Earth impactors\n",
    " - Find the numbers and names (if they exist) of Atens discovered in 1992\n",
    " - Retrieve the names and citations of all interstellar objects\n",
    "\n",
    "The List API is a REST endpoint. You can send GET requests to:\n",
    "\n",
    "    https://data.minorplanetcenter.net/api/list\n",
    "\n",
    "In the examples below we use Python code to query the API.\n",
    "\n",
    "Further information and documentation can be found at:\n",
    " - https://docs.minorplanetcenter.net/mpc-ops-docs/apis/list/\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7b8a604d-2129-42b2-96d0-10b5c0bee470",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Import Packages\n",
    "Here we import the standard Python packages needed to call the API and interpret the returned data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "18ae80f3-d99f-4868-8a38-3b81a5c2a449",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import requests\n",
    "import json\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "api-params-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# API Parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "The Observatory Codes API accepts the following parameters:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Parameter | Type | Required | Description | Default |\n",
    "|-----------|------|----------|-------------|---------|\n",
    "| `list` | String | Yes | Type of object/names (see options below) | N/A |\n",
    "| `order` | String | No | Sort order, ascending (ASC) or descending (DESC) | ASC |\n",
    "| `limit` | Integer | No | Maximum number of results (1-50000) | 50000 |\n",
    "| `offset` | Integer | No | Index of first result to return | 0 |\n",
    "| `like` | String | No | Pattern for filtering provisional designations (PostgreSQL [LIKE syntax](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/functions-matching.html#FUNCTIONS-LIKE)) | None |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Options for types of objects to return\n",
    "\n",
    "Possible options for `list` include:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Object type | Description |\n",
    "| `minor-planets' | all minor planets |\n",
    "| `neos` | near-Earth objects |\n",
    "| `inners` | inner main belt asteroids |\n",
    "| `middles` | mid main belt asteroids |\n",
    "| `outers` | outer main belt asteroids |\n",
    "| `binaries` | binary minor planets |\n",
    "| `comets` | comets |\n",
    "| `fragments` | pieces that broke off a minor planet |\n",
    "| `atiras` | Atiras |\n",
    "| `atens` | Atens |\n",
    "| `apollos` | Apollos |\n",
    "| `amors` | Amors |\n",
    "| `inner-others` | other inner main belt asteroids |\n",
    "| `mars-crossers` | astroids that cross Mars's orbit |\n",
    "| `main-belters` | main-belt asteroids |\n",
    "| `jovian-trojans` | Jupiter Trojan asteroids |\n",
    "| `tnos` | trans-Neptunian (distant) objects |\n",
    "| `hyperbolics` | objects with strongly unbound orbits |\n",
    "| `parabolics` | objects with eccentricityâ‰ˆ1 |\n",
    "| `unbounded` | objects with eccentricityâ‰¥1 |\n",
    "| `planet-nat-sats` | natural satellites of major planets |\n",
    "| `mp-nat-sats` | natural satellites of minor planets |\n",
    "| `impacted` | minor planets that collided with a larger body |\n",
    "| `retired` | minor planets that do not/no longer exist |\n",
    "| `dual-status` | objects that are both comets and minor planets |\n",
    "| `minor-planet-names` | names of minor planets |\n",
    "| `nat-sat-names` | names of natural satellites of major planets |\n",
    "| `comet-names` | names of comets |\n",
    "| `interstellar-names` | names of interstellar objects |\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "examples intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
   "# Example queries\n",
   "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "72bd5357-0123-448b-9614-5c449a1d25ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Query for list of Earth impactors\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we query for objects that have impacted the Earth and their locations and times of impact."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1d1067e7-5b7f-456f-bd09-69034e8280ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Query for Earth impactors\n",
    "response = requests.get(\n",
    "    \"https://data.minorplanetcenter.net/api/list\",\n",
    "    json={\"list\": \"impacted\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "if response.ok:\n",
    "    result = response.json()\n",
    "    print(json.dumps(result, indent=4))\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"Error: {response.status_code}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "response-fields-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Response Fields\n",
    "\n",
    "The JSON response includes these fields:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Field | Description |\n",
    "|-------|-------------|\n",
    "| `citation` | information about the object name |\n",
    "| `group` | object type |\n",
    "| `name` | object name |\n",
    "| `orbital_parameters` | orbit elements (currently null) |\n",
    "| `permid` | object number |\n",
    "| `reference` | publication info (currently null) |\n",
    "| `unpacked_primary_provisional_designation` | provisional (pre-numbering) object name |\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "interstellar-obj-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Interstellar objects\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we gather info on the names of the second and third discovered interstellar objects."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "interstellar-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Query for interstellar object names\n",
    "response = requests.get(\n",
    "    \"https://data.minorplanetcenter.net/api/list\",\n",
    "    json={\"list\": \"interstellar-names\",\n",
    "          \"limit\": 2,\n",
    "          \"offset\": 1}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "if response.ok:\n",
    "    result = response.json()\n",
    "    print(json.dumps(result, indent=4))\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"Error: {response.status_code}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "atens-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Query for Atens discovered in 1992\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we query for all Atens with discovery observations made in 1992."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "atens-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get Atens with 1992 in provid\n",
    "response = requests.get(\n",
    "    \"https://data.minorplanetcenter.net/api/list\",\n",
    "    json={\"list\": \"atens\"\n",
    "          \"like\": \"1992%\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "if response.ok:\n",
    "    result = response.json()\n",
    "    print(json.dumps(result, indent=4))\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"Error: {response.status_code}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "summary-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "The MPC List API provides access to lists of objects catalogued by the MPC.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key points:\n",
    "- **Endpoint**: `https://data.minorplanetcenter.net/api/list`\n",
    "- **List names and associated info of to 50,000 objects of type <objecttype>**: `{\"list\": \"<objecttype>\"}`\n",
    "- **Key fields**: `list`, `limit`, `like`, `offset`, `order`\n",
    "\n",
    "For questions or feedback, contact the MPC via the [Jira Helpdesk](https://mpc-service.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/13/create/148)."
   ]
  }
